An entity manager is defined to be of a given transactional type—either JTA or resource-local—at the time its underlying entity manager factory is config ured and created. See sections 8.2.1.2 and 9.1.

	<persistence-unit name="##generated" transaction-type="JTA">
	<persistence-unit name="##generated" transaction-type="RESOURCE_LOCAL">
